# 8. 交響する音と心と

Shiho: Well then, let's do it.
An: Okay! Here we go!
An: ♪——! ——! ——!
Shiho: ...!
Shiho: (Flying right out the gates...)
Shiho: (It's like she's telling me to hurry up and join in. How should I do that?)
Shiho: (I'll start like this...)
An: (...! This really is such a good sound!)
An: ♪————!! ♪————!!
Shiho: (Shiraishi's singing sounds nicer than it did earlier. She's drawing out the notes and echoing into the distance.)
Shiho: (It doesn't have that heart-rending feeling. She sounds like she's having so much fun...and I think I'm getting that same energy myself.)
Shiho: (I've gotta match singing like this...)
An: (Oh... Hinomori's playing just changed a little.)
An: (It's a really clean sound, just like before. And she has this unique groove. I'm hooked.)
An: (She really sounds like she's having fun, too. I can hear her getting more and more into it.)
An: (But she's not having all the fun...!)
An: ♪————!! ————!!
Shiho: (Shiraishi... So she can sing like this too. Nice.)
Shiho: (Next, let's...)
Nene: “I cannot sing...”
Nene: No... That doesn't sound right. I want to get closer to the Cowardly Canary...
Nene: I need to get closer...
Nene: *Sigh*
Nene: (I'm a little scared of this street, so I came to try and empathize with the Cowardly Canary's fear of the forest...)
Nene: (But I don't think this will be enough to get into character...)
Nene: (I've gotta find a different way to practice. Once I have a good method, if I just keep at it...)
Nene: (But... Will that really...?)
???: ♪————
Nene: (Hm? Someone's singing? Oh, is that...?)
Nene: Shiraishi and...Hinomori?
An: ♪————!!
Nene: Whoa...
Nene: (I didn't know they could perform that well.)
Nene: I have to do the same.
Nene: If I really want to close the gap, I need to give it all I have. Or else, I'll never get there...
Shiho: *Sigh*
An: That was so much fun! We ended up doing a whole bunch of songs!
An: You threw in these really good phrases at just the right parts, so I got more and more into it!
Shiho: Hehe, so did I. And you sang really well.
Shiho: You sing with so much power, Shiraishi. I brought out all the techniques I know just now.
An: Yeah! You had me electrified with that sound! What was that?!
Shiho: I copied that playing style from a certain musician a while back, just for the heck of it.
Shiho: I don't normally use it, so it was a good opportunity to try it out.
Shiho: Speaking of which, didn't you also change up the rhythm suddenly?
An: Huh? I guess I just felt like it. It's no surprise since you did something new with the bass every time I mixed it up.
An: But thanks to all that, we had a real good time!
???: Um, excuse me...
An: Huh?
Shiho: Kusanagi?
An: Hey, what brings you to this neck of the woods? What a pleasant surprise!
Nene: Oh, um... I was out for a walk, and then I heard you two...
An: Oh, really? We weren't being too loud, were we? We were really getting into it.
Nene: No, it's nothing like that. But...
Nene: Would it be okay if...I sang with you?
An: Yes, of course!
An: Right, Hinomori?
Shiho: Sure, let's have a session together.
Nene: *Gasp* Th-Thank you...
Shiho: Alright, let's start.
An: Okay!
An & Nene: ————♪
Nene: (They really are amazing...)
Nene: (It's like Hinomori's bass is pushing us forward.)
Nene: (Also...)
