Shiho: Thanks.
Shiho: We promise to make it one worth looking forward to.
Miku: <That was a really good session, wasn't it?>
Shiho: Oh, Miku. You were listening to us?
Miku: <I was, yes. I'm guessing it was a good chance to relax for you, Shiho?>
Shiho: Yeah... I'm glad we got to perform together. I feel energized in the run-up to the real thing.
Shiho: Miku, I... I'm glad that I'm a musician.
Miku: <Why do you say that?>
Shiho: It's because I continued with music that I was able to come this far with the others. And I wouldn't have been able to perform like I did today if I hadn't.
Miku: <Hehe, I guess so.>
Miku: <I think you have the potential to grow even more, Shiho.>
Miku: <And the same goes for them.>
Shiho: Yeah, you're right.
Shiho: (I'm going to keep delivering the best performances with the others. And...)
Shiho: (Whether it's during practice, at the solo show or somewhere we haven't even reached yet...)
Shiho: (I never want to stop playing my bass with them.)
